parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of braking power, and unpredictable vehicle behavior, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: ABS light on or off intermittently
grinding or warped brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel speed sensor can cause the ABS to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances and loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: ABS light on or off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Rotors and Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of rotors can lead to brake failure, causing loss of braking power and increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
The failure of the brake clip can cause loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
The failure of the transmission shift interlock can cause the transmission selector to become stuck in park, leading to accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle rolls unexpectedly.
symptoms: The transmission selector will not move out of park
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly while in park
the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting into drive or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission solenoid can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle loses power while in motion.
symptoms: the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting into drive or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission reverse gear can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to shift into reverse
the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting into drive or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially at slow speeds.
symptoms: The key intermittently fails to turn in the ignition switch
the vehicle stalls at slow speeds
the steering wheel must be turned several times before the vehicle will start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Control Module/PROM can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
